<item>
            <title>[LU-16033] refine ll_use_fast_io() for stride mode</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-16033</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;ll_use_fast_io() calculates whether current readahead window covers next_readahead + max rpc pages, if that&apos;s the case, we can issue a readahed RPC, so we&apos;d not do fast IO because we will need a cl_io to issue the RPC, otherwise we&apos;d return true and do fast IO w/o issueing readahead RPC.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;While for stride mode, the to-be-covered pages algorithm is&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
max_rpc_pages * (ras-&amp;gt;ras_stride_length + ras-&amp;gt;ras_stride_bytes - 1) / stride_bytes&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;which is not so accurate.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
